h3. Summary
The */rest/servicedeskapi/request* endpoint is returning {{Internal Server Error}} instead of the correct error message for requests sending null values in the body

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Send a REST request to the */rest/servicedeskapi/request* endpoint having a null value in the body. E.g.:
{noformat}
{  
   "requestTypeId":"ID_OF_REQUEST_TYPE",
   "serviceDeskId":1,
   
   "requestFieldValues":{  
      "description":"TEST DESCRIPTION",
      "summary":"Test TEST",
      "attachment": null
   }
} 
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
Either a service request is created or a meaningful error message is returned

h3. Actual Results
Error {{500 - Internal Server Error}} is returned and the screen "Oops something went wrong" is displayed.

However, the correct/meaningful error message is logged by JIRA: {{null value in entry: attachment=null}}
{noformat}
com.atlassian.plugins.rest.common.error.jersey.ThrowableExceptionMapper	Uncaught exception thrown by REST service: Instantiation of [simple type, class com.atlassian.servicedesk.api.rest.dto.domain.request.RequestCreateDTO] value failed: null value in entry: attachment=null	......
{noformat}
 

h3.Workaround
No workaround at the moment.
